Men are not robots they feel just like us women do. Aren’t we all human ?

Suppressing emotions and feelings doesn’t make anyone strong. It slowly eats you up and will come out in some way shape or form. We can’t avoid that. 

We must allow ourselves and our children to FEEL whatever is felt because our feelings and their feelings are valid. We feel it, we process it, make sense of it and then we are able to let it go. Co regulation with children is so important before they are able to regulate their own feelings. Brain development is key, don’t forget that. They are not adults. 

We don’t want to be haunted by un acknowledged emotions that we push down to the bottom in the name of being “strong”. Vulnerability is strength. Through honoring this we can learn to better work through and control our emotions when necessary. At times it is necessary to have the ability to control them but again it does not mean we suppress them. 

@raiseherwild 🖤

Conscious Parenting or gentle parenting gets misunderstood by many. Rules and boundaries are still established that’s a must,however, children are allowed to be children, they are not shamed for FEELING big feelings and being unable to regulate themselves. The developmental stages of children are acknowledged and taken into account. Connection with the child is seeked by the parent instead of punishment for being human. What happened to us as children is not our kids fault and subconsciously teaching them and giving them our wounds, insecurities and traumas isn’t fair. 

As parents let’s work on ourselves so that we can be the best examples to our children and allow them to grow into who they are freely. So much to talk about with this, I’m going to do many videos on it and my perspective and experience with my son, as well as many personal development and conscious parenting clients. 
.

So proud of my boy! We spoke about being on stage for weeks. He didn’t want to. We spoke about things he could do to help him if he was nervous or scared. We practiced. I told him I would make sure I was in the front rows  and that he was safe, strong and capable. The first time he went up onstage he was upset and of course all I wanted to do was go and take him off stage and hug him and sit him with me. His amazing teacher noticed he was upset and hugged him while he was on stage. She comforted him and that meant so much to us. 

I knew they had to come back out to walk and get their certificates, I closed my eyes and reminded him he could do it, he was powerful. My boy put on his shades and although he wasn’t exactly thrilled, he pushed through it and went back up not once but two more times. I use to have crazy stage fright so I get it, it’s an awful feeling. The fact that he did it means so much and makes me so damn proud! Congrats baby boy you are so amazing ! Off to kindergarten! 🎓🧑‍🎓

There are many reasons “why” from cutting things out drastically from day 1 and then binging or not eating enough or eating too much, the list goes on. I always say prepare to succeed. There may be different ways to reach your goals but one thing is for certain it’s going to take discipline and hard work!
